         <abstract>
            <p>A collocation procedure is developed for the initial value problem u'(t) = f(t, u(t)), u(0) = 0, using the globally defined sinc basis functions. It is shown that this sinc procedure converges to the solution at an exponential rate, i.e., &lt;tex-math&gt;$\mathcal{O}(M^2 \exp(-\kappa\sqrt M))$&lt;/tex-math&gt; where &lt;latex&gt;$\kappa &gt; 0$&lt;/latex&gt; and 2M basis functions are used in the expansion. Problems on the domains R = (-∞, ∞) and R&lt;sup&gt;+&lt;/sup&gt; = (0, ∞) are used to illustrate the implementation and accuracy of the procedure.</p>
          </abstract>
